  "body": "*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When I send ETH in 1-1 or group chat and internet connection is suddenly lost, I recieve error message \"Post https://rosten.infura.io/z6GCTmjdP3FETEJmMBI4:read tcp 172.20.10.3:35829->54.88.141.252:443:read:software caused connection abort\"\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nError message 'No internet connection'\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nError message \"Post https://rosten.infura.io...\" when internet connection drops during transaction.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Use Hotspot (from another device)\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Navigate to any Chat\r\n- Use command /send 0 ETH\r\n- Tap Enter\r\n- Tap Sign transaction\r\n- Enter you password\r\n- Turn off Hotspot\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: release\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n![lg1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36479997/36563016-e384e1e4-1829-11e8-9e65-8ed2586ce1ec.png)\r\n",
